<node CREATED="1566553719058" ID="ID_1302012834" MODIFIED="1566553719058" TEXT="An extended context-free grammar (or regular right part grammar) is one in which the right-hand side of the production rules is allowed to be a regular expression over the grammars terminals and nonterminals. Extended context-free grammars describe exactly the context-free languages." />
