<node CREATED="1566553719058" ID="ID_1772175662" MODIFIED="1566553719058" TEXT="A context-free grammar (CFG) consists of a set of productions that you use to replace a vari-able by a string of variables and terminals. The language of a grammar is the set of strings it generates. A language is context-free if there is a CFG for it. Goddard 6a: 20" />
