<node CREATED="1566553719058" ID="ID_718107787" MODIFIED="1566553719058" TEXT="Context-free languages (CFLs) are generated by context-free grammars. The set of all context-free languages is identical to the set of languages accepted by pushdown automata and the set of regular languages is a subset of context-free languages. An inputed language is accepted by a computational model if it runs through the model and ends in an accepting final state." />
