<node CREATED="1566553719074" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_829974448" LINK="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chomsky_Normal_Form" MODIFIED="1566553719074" TEXT="Chomsky normal form - Wikipedia">
<node CREATED="1566553719074" ID="ID_962387640" MODIFIED="1566553719074" TEXT="In formal language theory a context-free grammar G is said to be in Chomsky normal form (first described by Noam Chomsky) if all of its production rules are of the form:: 92&#226;&#8364;&#8220;93106. A &#226;&#8224;&#8217; BC or A &#226;&#8224;&#8217; a or S &#226;&#8224;&#8217; &#206;&#181;. where A B and C are nonterminal symbols a is a terminal symbol (a symbol that represents a constant value) S is the start symbol and &#206;&#181; denotes the empty string." />
