<node CREATED="1566553719076" ID="ID_1975092255" MODIFIED="1566553719076" TEXT="In the formal languages of computer science and linguistics the Chomsky hierarchy (occasionally referred to as the Chomsky-Sch&#195;&#188;tzenberger hierarchy) is a containment hierarchy of classes of formal grammars.. This hierarchy of grammars was described by Noam Chomsky in 1956. It is also named after Marcel-Paul Sch&#195;&#188;tzenberger who played a crucial role in the development of the theory of formal " />
