<node CREATED="1566553719076" ID="ID_1112139951" MODIFIED="1566553719076" TEXT="2. The Chomsky hierarchy. A formal language in the sense of FLT is a set of sequences or strings over some finite vocabulary &#206;&#163;.When applied to natural languages the vocabulary is usually identified with words morphemes or sounds. 2 FLT is a collection of mathematical and algorithmic tools about how to define formal languages with finite means and how to process them computationally." />
