<node CREATED="1566553719082" ID="ID_1628941846" MODIFIED="1566553719082" TEXT="Since there is a one-to-one correspondence between linear-bounded automata and such grammars no more tape than that occupied by the original string is necessary for the string to be recognized by the automaton. History. In 1960 John Myhill introduced an automaton model today known as deterministic linear bounded automaton." />
