<node CREATED="1566553719090" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_979727343" LINK="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NP_(complexity)" MODIFIED="1566553719090" TEXT="NP (complexity) - Wikipedia">
<node CREATED="1566553719090" ID="ID_569682480" MODIFIED="1566553719090" TEXT="In computational complexity theory NP (nondeterministic polynomial time) is a complexity class used to classify decision problems.NP is the set of decision problems for which the problem instances where the answer is yes have proofs verifiable in polynomial time.. An equivalent definition of NP is the set of decision problems solvable in polynomial time by a non-deterministic Turing machine." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1566553719090" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1800989211" LINK="https://cs.stackexchange.com/questions/1243/what-is-meant-by-solvable-by-non-deterministic-algorithm-in-polynomial-time" MODIFIED="1566553719090" TEXT="What is meant by solvable by non deterministic algorithm ">
<node CREATED="1566553719090" ID="ID_1499161472" MODIFIED="1566553719090" TEXT="Informally the main difference between nondeterministic algorithms and the normal deterministic algorithms is that when provided with multiple choices to take the deterministic solution will have to check one of them at a time in sequence while the nondeterministic version can cheat a bit." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1566553719090" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_347464247" LINK="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/NP-Problem.html" MODIFIED="1566553719090" TEXT="NP-Problem -- from Wolfram MathWorld">
<node CREATED="1566553719090" ID="ID_1830324172" MODIFIED="1566553719090" TEXT="NP-Problem. A problem is assigned to the NP (nondeterministic polynomial time) class if it is solvable in polynomial time by a nondeterministic Turing machine.. A P-problem (whose solution time is bounded by a polynomial) is always also NP. If a problem is known to be NP and a solution to the problem is somehow known then demonstrating the correctness of the solution can always be reduced to " />
</node>
<node CREATED="1566553719091" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_961518988" LINK="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nondeterministic_algorithm" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="Nondeterministic algorithm - Wikipedia">
<node CREATED="1566553719091" ID="ID_502649418" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="An algorithm that solves a problem in nondeterministic polynomial time can run in polynomial time or exponential time depending on the choices it makes during execution. The nondeterministic algorithms are often used to find an approximation to a solution when the exact solution would be too costly to obtain using a deterministic one." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1566553719091" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1323536467" LINK="https://encyclopedia2.thefreedictionary.com/nondeterministic+polynomial+time" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="Nondeterministic polynomial time | Article about ">
<node CREATED="1566553719091" ID="ID_562057695" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="nondeterministic polynomial time (complexity) (NP) A set or property of computational decision problems solvable by a nondeterministic Turing Machine in a number of steps that is a polynomial function of the size of the input. The word nondeterministic suggests a method of generating potential solutions using some form of nondeterminism or trial and " />
</node>
<node CREATED="1566553719091" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_221297661" LINK="http://umsl.edu/~siegelj/information_theory/classassignments/Lombardo/03_nondeterministicpolynomialtime.html" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="Nondeterministic polynomial time - University of Missouri ">
<node CREATED="1566553719091" ID="ID_1088846101" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="Nondeterministic polynomial time . A verifier for a language A is an algorithm V where A = {w | V accepts  wc  for some string c}.. We measure the time of a verifier only in terms of the length of w so a polynomial time verifier runs in polynomial time in the length of w.. A language A is polynomially verifiable if it has a polynomial time verifier.. NP is the class of languages that have " />
</node>
<node CREATED="1566553719091" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_425687934" LINK="https://searchsecurity.techtarget.com/definition/P-versus-NP" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="What is P versus NP (polynomial versus nondeterministic ">
<node CREATED="1566553719091" ID="ID_133186206" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="P versus NP (polynomial versus nondeterministic polynomial) refers to a theoretical question presented in 1971 by Leonid Levin and Stephen Cook concerning mathematical problems that are easy to " />
</node>
<node CREATED="1566553719091" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1985761217" LINK="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/40207550/np-non-deterministic-polynomial-time" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="algorithm - NP - Non deterministic polynomial time - Stack ">
<node CREATED="1566553719091" ID="ID_1304800984" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="NP - Non deterministic polynomial time.  So a nondeterministic algorithm can open all n doors at the same time; hence 1 operations to find the prize. Now an example of something that can be solved polynomially using nondeterminism. Let&#226;&#8364;&#8482;s say you are faced with 2 doors (at depth 1) you choose one and you again see 2 doors (at depth 2 " />
</node>
<node CREATED="1566553719091" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_272110500" LINK="http://foldoc.org/nondeterministic%20polynomial%20time" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="nondeterministic polynomial time from FOLDOC">
<node CREATED="1566553719091" ID="ID_1286632655" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="nondeterministic polynomial time complexity (NP) A set or property of computational decision problems solvable by a nondeterministic Turing Machine in a number of steps that is a polynomial function of the size of the input. The word nondeterministic suggests a method of generating potential solutions using some form of nondeterminism or trial and error." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1566553719091" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_379671144" LINK="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/38673541/non-deterministic-polynomialnp-vs-polynomialp" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="algorithm - Non deterministic Polynomial(NP) vs Polynomial ">
<node CREATED="1566553719091" ID="ID_1648243961" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="NP(nondeterministic polynomial Problem):-Now there are a lot of programs that dont (necessarily) run in polynomial time on a regular computer but do run in polynomial time on a nondeterministic Turing machine. These programs solve problems in NP which stands for nondeterministic polynomial time." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1566553719091" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_427362261" LINK="https://cs.stackexchange.com/questions/85030/what-is-difference-between-nondeterministic-polynomial-time-and-exponential-time" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="What is difference between nondeterministic polynomial ">
<node CREATED="1566553719091" ID="ID_257377799" MODIFIED="1566553719091" TEXT="The class of problems solvable by a nondeterministic Turing Machine in polynomial time is $\mathsf{NP}$ for Nondeterministic polynomial time. This definition has nothing to do with exponential time or exponential functions at all. The class of problems solvable by a deterministic Turing Machine in exponential time is $\mathsf{EXP}$." />
</node>
