<node CREATED="1566553719093" ID="ID_611367855" MODIFIED="1566553719093" TEXT="Overview. NP-complete problems are in NP the set of all decision problems whose solutions can be verified in polynomial time; NP may be equivalently defined as the set of decision problems that can be solved in polynomial time on a non-deterministic Turing machine.A problem p in NP is NP-complete if every other problem in NP can be transformed (or reduced) into p in polynomial time." />
</node>
